    • Method Detail

      • print

        public static void print(java.lang.String msg,
                         java.lang.Object... swap)
        Prints a string with parameters inside the string (rendition of C's printf()). Replaces %a, then %b, then %c, etc.

        Example:
        print("Here is a String: %a, and here is another object: %b", "hello", 12345);

        Note: creates an alias for the message string.
        Parameters:
        msg - The string with % parameters.
        swap - The objects to be swapped in.
